From 29046b9b99c1d3aa38c5252c75a2ee41a7b457cc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Timo V <timiv@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Tue, 10 Mar 2026 20:15:20 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] sunxi: r528: add display support with RB channel swap

Add display pipeline support for the Allwinner R528/T113s SoC:
- PLL_VIDEO0 clock functions (clock_sun50i_h6.h/c)
- DE2 base addresses for NCAT2 (cpu_sunxi_ncat2.h)
- Kconfig: enable SUNXI_DE2 for R528, fix VIDEO_DW_HDMI dependencies
- LCDC PLL configuration for NCAT2 (lcdc.c)
- DE2 composer initialization for NCAT2 (sunxi_de2.c)
- LCD pinmux, bus gate and reset for R528 (sunxi_lcd.c)
- Makefile fix for conditional HDMI compilation
- RB channel swap support via TCON0_CTL bit 23 (lcdc.h, sunxi_lcd.c)
  controlled by sunxi,rb-swap DT property

Upstream-Status: Pending [Not submitted to upstream yet]
